BROWN SPOT, RICE - BHUTAN: (MONGAR)
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 1 Nov 2018
Source: Kuensel Online [edited]
http://www.kuenselonline.com/pest-and-brown-spot-disease-infest-paddy-fields-in-saling/


Following an outbreak of pest and brown spot disease in their paddy fields recently, farmers in Mongar [district] are worried about the yield. Some leased landholders said they won't be able to return the landowner's share if the harvest is not good.

[The local] agriculture extension [office] said, the pest and disease outbreak has occurred due to climate change and farmers using old stock seeds. [They] had suggested affected farmers apply urea to retain the plants and had also distributed spray machines and pesticides. However, some farmers are reluctant to apply chemical fertilisers and pesticides.

A team from agriculture research and development center [of the Bhutan Ministry of Agriculture & Forests] in Wengkhar also visited and inspected the affected paddy fields.

[Byline: Tashi Phuntsho]

